commentBody:
@Jake G
I agree with Steve that “Hot spot” as a clue for DESERT  is questionable, at best. Yes, misdirection is a highlight of the late-week puzzles, and is part of what makes those puzzles puzzling (and fun!)— but appropriate misdirection does not necessitate being misleading. In this puzzle, 2-D is, in my opinion, a great example of misdirection: despite my smattering of Spanish, and clearly knowing that “once” means “eleven” in that language, NUMERO filled in through crosses, and it wasn’t until I read the column after completion that I “got it”— and had my “d’oh” moment! There was nothing misleading about the clue, it just required thinking outside the box.

Despite this nit, and the fact that the solve was significantly quicker solve than my average Friday, I did enjoy this puzzle.

