The car license/number plates and street signs point to a European country. Looks like maybe they drive on the left, but I can't be sure. Cyclists on the sidewalk is also a clue - in a place like Netherlands they'd have a dedicated bike lane. Things get too fuzzy when I zoom in too much, but it looks like a 30 in a red circle on the white sign - if that's a speed limit, I think 30mph is a bit fast for that area/intersection, I'd guess it's 30kph...

So, my guess is a European country where they drive on the left and speeds are kph, where cyclists use the sidewalks... but that's as far as I can guess.

