@MOL
My film reel breaking story:

On a snowy, blustery January weeknight in the winter of 1986, my roommate and I trekked about 10 Manhattan blocks to catch a 1030ish o'clock showing of Out of Africa.  There were about 40 people in a huge theater. About 10 minutes before the end, just as Redford left to go on another trip, the film breaks. Quelle horreur! After a bit, the projectist comes out to tell us he can't fix it, no other employees were there, and he would give everyone passes to come back.  No one would leave until he told us the end of the movie. Even though we all had a pretty good idea.

